        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "feat(auth): Add 1Password keyring backend",
        "body": "gog currently supports OS keychain and encrypted file storage, but local agent workflows that rely on macOS Keychain can hit repeated approval prompts. This adds a 1Password keyring backend so users can store gog OAuth refresh tokens in a 1Password API Credential item instead.\n\nThe backend supports both local desktop-app auth and service-account auth. Non-secret 1Password settings can be configured through `gog config`, while `OP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN` remains environment-only for headless use.\n\nExample setup:\n\n```bash\ngog auth keyring 1password\ngog config set onepassword_auth desktop\ngog config set onepassword_account 'Your 1Password account name'\ngog config set onepassword_vault <vault-id>\ngog auth list --check\n```\n\nThis is the backend-only slice from the previous 1Password work. The access-token cache is deliberately left out so the storage backend can be reviewed independently.",
